<br />

<br />
The #1 area that the Magician community would like to see a response from the developers is the return of the days when the mage could depend on our pet as a viable source of dps/defense for the content the we are fighting. 
<br />

<br />
Due to the fact that at lvl 58 and higher a magician could no longer count on the necessary dps/defensive abilities that their pet had provided them from lvls 4-57, there is a severe gap in our ability to be useful in a group or be a true soloing class beyond that level. 
<br />

<br />
Please review item #1 on our list as the most important item to the mage community. This one area when resolved will fix 95% of all of the class balancing requests of the mage community. We have taken polls on the subject and roughly 70% of mages agree that fixing broken pets and improving our pets DPS/survivability is the only issue that truly matters. 
<br />

<br />
1.<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: blue">Improve pets</span></span></span></span></span> -  
<br />

<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Damage ability</span> (DPS upgrade, stats/hit consistency + accuracy /damage crits)  
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Survivability/Defense upgrade </span>(SVstats/Mitigation) 
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Utility</span> Rathe's Son and Child of Earth – Remove the proximity agro that root causes which makes our earth pet undesirable in groups and on raids. Possible solutions: (1) Replace root with 100% snare which will remove proximity agro but still have the same effect as root plus it will not break on nukes.  (2) Re-code pet root with proximity agro component removed.
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Fix our lvl 51 and higher fire pet</span> This pet has been broken for 4 years. It is so bad that mages no longer use it. Our repeated requests for fire pets to be fixed, although we have presented several solutions, this project has yet to be addressed and completed.    
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Revamp pet focus availability/drop rates</span> - Give us a way to obtain/quest/upgrade pet focuses beyond Summoners boon. 
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Upgrade our summoned focus items, pet armor and weapons </span>- our brand new OoW pet weapons do no additional damage than the PoP era summoned weapons. Pet only items should have new procs like slow, snarelure and rune. Pet focus items should scale better with OoW era content.
<br />

<br />
2. <span style="font-weight: bold">Fix GoD Nuke Imbalance</span> -
<br />

<br />
The recent improvements to Bolt of Jerikor are a partial solution. Our new BoJ nuke should have 3120 base damage (FoT2K + 20% in GoD=Missing bolt in GoD 2.6K + 30% = BoJ 3120 in OoW), See this link: <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?p=227377&highlight=#227377" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?p=227377&highlight=#227377</a>
<br />

<br />
3. <span style="font-weight: bold">Improve pet heals </span>
<br />

<br />
-Shorter cast times, shorter recast times 
<br />
-Have pet focus (DPOC, MoD, MoE, MoDis) enhance pet heals 
<br />
-Increase heal amount
<br />

<br />
4. <span style="font-weight: bold">COTH utility</span>
<br />

<br />
-Make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones. If a small area of the zone is necessary to have both coth/corpse summon blocked for potential exploit reasons then just block that small area of the zone. 
<br />
-Cross zone coth
<br />

<br />
5. <span style="font-weight: bold">Update Rains</span> 
<br />

<br />
-Our high end OoW rains cannot be chain casted. Please remove the grey out blocker/locker on the casting times.
<br />
-Remove the innate resists on Rains, and retune the mana cost on many rains "See <a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target="_blank">http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html</a> for details.
<br />

<br />

<br />
6.defer to fixing pets
<br />
7.defer to fixing pets
<br />
8.defer to fixing pets
<br />
9.defer to fixing pets
<br />
10.defer to fixing pets
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-weight: bold">Note to PvP correspondent/developers:</span></span> 
<br />

<br />
-Have pets be treated like PC’s instead of NPC’s for spell resists, damage, etc. See this link for detail: <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&highlight=" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&highlight=</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Note: Items set to go live soon, but held up</span>:
<br />

<br />
-Making pet be able to survive invisibility 
<br />
-Targeted summons to hit live server. (possible solution make it just for pets?)<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"></span><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="text-decoration: underline"></span></span><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/dtresendes/danisig.png" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639739" target="_blank" class="postlink">Danille Impholder</a>
<br />
Ayonae Ro ~ Vallis Aspectus
